question.title: Will Q's market close price on 2026-02-26 be higher than its market close price on 2026-02-20?
question.description:
Qnity Electronics, Inc. is a company that is listed on the S&P 500 index. It's ticker is Q. It's last close price as of the creation of this question (2026-02-16 20:41:24) is 111.69. You can find more information about Qnity Electronics, Inc. at https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/Q

Qnity Electronics, Inc. provides materials and solutions to the semiconductor and electronics industries in the United States, rest of Americas, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, Asia Pacific, China, South Korea, Taiwan, and internationally. It operates in two segments, Semiconductor Technologies and Interconnect Solutions. The company offers chemical mechanical planarization (CMP) pads and slurries, photoresists, functional sub-layers, advanced overcoats, post-CMP cleaners, post-etch residue removers, and emerging cleans. It also provides copper pillar plating, copper redistribution layer, solder bump plating, under bump metallization, photoresists, packaging dielectrics, gap fillers, phase change, specialty thermal interface materials, thermally conductive insulators, copper playing solutions, dry film photoresists, and laminates and polyimide films. The company sells its products under the Advanced Cleans, Circuposit, Duroptix, Kalrez, Lithojet, Metallization, Pyralux, Riston, Acuplane, EPIC, Ikonic, Kapton, Laird, Microfill, Solderon, and Silveron brands. Its products are used in advanced cleans solutions, CMP, circuit imaging materials, connectors, general metal finishing, laminates, leadframes, metallization, microlithography, semiconductor packaging materials, and tape automated bonding applications. The company serves aerospace, electronics, industrial, oil and gas, and transportation industries. The company was formerly known as Novus SpinCo 1, Inc. and changed its name to Qnity Electronics, Inc. in April 2025. The company was incorporated in 2024 and is headquartered in Wilmington, Delaware.
